Manage Email Preferences
Not you?
Privacy Policy
Opt out or contact us anytime




‚ÄúWe were taking a product that was in the marketplace and we were bringing it to market maybe a year later,‚Äù Ms. Stanton said. ‚ÄúAnd our designers were designing for somebody else. So you used to get design teams say: ‚ÄòWell, I‚Äôm not sure if I‚Äôd wear that, but it‚Äôs O.K. for Old Navy.‚Äô¬†‚ÄùMs. Stanton instead pushed to build Old Navy‚Äôs own design muscle, leaning on Gap‚Äôs supply chain to allow designers to quickly test various prints, shapes and sizes in small runs in stores before increasing the production of styles that were with a hit with shoppers. It shifted its collection from everyday or basic items to others that were on-trend and in season. Instead of hiring designers whose experience was in the low-price market, Old Navy hired top talent: an accessories and bag designer from Coach, athletic wear designers from Nike and Reebok, the men‚Äôs apparel director from North Face. (‚ÄúThey don‚Äôt start with cheap,‚Äù Ms. Stanton said.) Old Navy‚Äôs new ads, starring two comedy favorites, Amy Poehler and Julia Louis-Dreyfus, have gone viral.One of Old Navy‚Äôs biggest triumphs has been its pixie pants. Two years ago, just as Mr. Larsson‚Äôs team was getting the label‚Äôs new look off the ground, a designer on Old Navy‚Äôs women‚Äôs team noticed that blogs and runways were filling up with casual, slim-fitting pants. The design team ‚Äúobsessed over every detail‚Äù ‚Äî the fit, the cut just above the ankle ‚Äî and quickly tested different prints and colors in stores. The pants were a hit.‚ÄúWe uniquely designed that pant, and then we put it to market and we tested it and we sold 2.4 million pairs last year,‚Äù Mr. Larsson said. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs one of the biggest revenue-generating styles that we have.‚ÄùMr. Larsson is on the hunt for his next big product.‚ÄúIf you were at Apple, nobody would say, ‚ÄòLet‚Äôs relaunch the iPhone 6.‚Äô People would laugh, and say that‚Äôs crazy. But that‚Äôs what happens in the fashion industry,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúIf you keep competing with generic products, and a higher and higher discount, you‚Äôre going to lose. If Apple doesn‚Äôt continuously refresh its products and make them current, they‚Äôre dead. And that would happen here as well.‚ÄùA new area that Old Navy has thrown itself into is active wear, for the first time investing heavily in performance fabrics, like breathable textiles. With sportswear, Old Navy is tapping into a trend that has swept through fashion, as sneakers and yoga pants take the place of jeans and pumps. But where a pair of yoga pants from Lululemon might cost almost $100, the same amount would outfit an entire family in performance wear at Old Navy, Ms. Stanton said.There are big challenges ahead for the company. For one, it starts to be compared against a year of strong sales, making further growth particularly difficult. In the first quarter of the year, same-store sales growth at Old Navy slowed to 3 percent, though it remained the fastest-growing Gap label.Rising wages overseas, as well as heightened scrutiny over working conditions at Gap‚Äôs foreign suppliers, also raise concerns over Old Navy‚Äôs low-price business model.

Advertisement

Continue reading the main story

Some analysts also wonder whether the recent jobs growth or savings from gas prices will prompt some shoppers to graduate from Old Navy, rising up the luxury ladder. Mr. Larsson says he does not think so. Snobbishness in fashion is on its way out, he says, especially among younger generations.‚ÄúThe industry is traditionally built on the ladder, but I don‚Äôt know if people aspire to that anymore,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúTimes are changing, and prestige is being looked at differently.‚Äù Young shoppers, especially, will always want to save ‚Äî ‚Äúthen they want to travel, experience things,‚Äù he said.‚ÄúSometimes when I shop at high-end brands, I get this look when I walk in, like people working there are screening me and asking: Are you good enough to be our customer?‚Äù Mr. Larsson said. ‚ÄúI hate it. And Old Navy is as an antidote to that.‚Äù
Continue reading the main story






We‚Äôre interested in your feedback on this page. Tell us what you think.







